##"We are connected to the real world, " says a group of 2000 students

Micro-signal GQREPORT

Function introduction, record the rise and fall of the characters and changes in the value of the Times. Complete, true, in-depth, accurate non-fiction stories, sent to you every week.

After the new crown outbreak, many people spontaneously formed donor groups. Some Chinese students studying in Singapore have joined the ranks. Most of them are post-2000 generation students who donate materials worth about 130,000 yuan. They are not prominent among the large number of high-achieving groups. But the donation, which lasted six days, was the first civic action of their lives.

After the new crown outbreak, many people spontaneously formed donor groups. Some Chinese students studying in Singapore have joined the ranks. Most of them are post-2000 generation students who donate materials worth about 130,000 yuan. They are not prominent among the large number of high-achieving groups. But the donation, which lasted six days, was the first civic action of their lives.

❶

The outbreak changed everything

Huang Lei Ke changed into a gray plaid suit and a dark blue tie and sat in the audience at the recording scene of this is China on Oriental satellite TV. The 20-year-old, who had just taken the Gaokao in Singapore, had traveled from his hometown of Guangzhou to Shanghai to meet a favorite guest. After six hours of recording, Huang Leike walked out of the studio, turned on his cell phone and heard the news that the country's leader had "given important instructions on the outbreak of COVID-19 pneumonia. " He thought the situation was serious, i looked up and saw that everyone on Nanjing West Road was wearing masks.
For six hours without a cell phone, it was as if a crisis had struck. "scared. " It was January 20. The next day, Huang Lei Ke early in the morning to buy masks, bustling downtown Shanghai, he ran seven or eight pharmacies, convenience stores, has been unable to find one.
Huang Leike returned to his hometown of Guangzhou, southern life is still as usual, mask inventory is sufficient, an N95 mask $8. He saw the shopkeeper, who he knew well, taking apart a box full of masks, 500 of them, for $4,000.
The tension rose again on New Year's Eve. More than 20 members of the family gathered for New Year's Eve dinner. My aunt, who works in the Yuexiu District Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine, was absent. The Southern Hospital in Guangzhou began assembling a team of doctors to support Wuhan. He noticed that the team included military doctors with the rank of senior colonel, which means they had been practicing for more than 30 years. "everyone else is eating New Year's Eve dinner, but they are all wearing camouflage clothes and carrying backpacks. "
Huang Leike was born in a military family, from a great-grandfather to his father, four generations of people in the military. My father was 20 years old when he took part in the battle of Laoshan in 1985. The doctors at Southern Hospital were the same age as my father, who went to war. It was the first time he had ever felt connected to the epidemic in Wuhan.
But soon, things got out of hand, and the news of the hospital fund-raiser was everywhere. "I had no idea there was going to be a shortage of supplies, " he said in an interview, still incredulous.
My father and uncle were talking over dinner on New Year's Eve about the doctors'lack of protective clothing, goggles and N95 masks. He found it hard to understand how a soldier on the battlefield could be short of ammunition and food? They told him that the hospital does not usually reserve these materials, to buy through the Health Committee centralized bidding, now how have time to go through the process?
Huang Leike wants to buy some masks to donate. When he saw the news of the outbreak earlier, he kept an open mind and asked the boss of the canteen downstairs for the supplier's wechat account. But even if the money and pocket money to buy their New Year's Day all into masks, can only make up a box or two. Maybe we can get some friends and classmates together, buy some more and send them together? He studied in Singapore and graduated from Temasek Junior College in November 2019. At 8 pm on January 24, he launched the first ever group Chat Qr Code in Singapore's Sophomore Class, "Hello Everyone! This group chat in the form of funds to remotely support Wuhan. "
Wong Lei Ke, 20, a graduate of the Temasek Junior College.
See The news in the group, Liu Yan ru family of ten people's New Year's Eve dinner has just ended. Like Huang, Liu graduated from Raffles Junior College after completing the National College entrance examination in Singapore. On New Year's Eve, in her home in Xiamen, she was curled up on a sofa on Weibo, and saw the news that all the major hospitals in Wuhan were raising money for the society. Liu interpreted the hospital's actions as an indication of the severity of the outbreak.
Weibo searches were almost all about Wuhan, and Liu felt he couldn't stay out of it. Just in the group to see Huang Leike's proposal, she took the initiative to contact the stranger, simple greetings, she asked whether the group Chat Qr Code into another large group of international students. In addition, she also reminded Huang Leike, in order to increase the credibility of the fund-raising, should be detailed information on the use of the funds, including the source of information, including the name of manufacturers, shipping methods.
The supplier has not responded the message, Huang Lei Ke is anxious for the supply source. Previously, he was in the local Charity Association as Honorary President of the relatives have asked whether the donation or money, the other said donations can be purchased by the organization. He told Liu Yanru, if can not find the source of goods, direct donations. But Liu Yanru reminds him, "personal humble opinion, can in kind on in kind. " Huang Lei Ke replies a "cover face" expression, "understand, ha ha ha ha. "
Huang Leike sent the second edition call-up copy to Liu Yanru for advice. Aware of Liu Yanru's carefulness and caution, Huang Leike invited her to join the planning group.
Wen Yaoyigang entered Raffles Junior College, also in the New Year's Eve, she learned from the QQ group of Singaporean students fund-raising activities. I didn't think anything of it. I just scanned in the code. As a native of Wuhan, she was eager to do something, but didn't know what to do. When she left her hometown on Jan. 12, everything seemed normal, but at 5 a.m. on Jan. 23, when her mother suddenly told her that Wuhan was closed, she burst into tears, waking up her roommate, who was also from Wuhan, with her eyes swollen from crying. She doesn't know how it got this far.
In retrospect, from the beginning of November to early January, back to Wuhan for more than two months holiday, Wen tan found that "there are many people have a cold. ". After the media announced on January 9 that the pathogen of "pneumonia of unknown origin" was COVID-19, her parents reminded her to wear a mask when she went out. They also told Wen that when SARS broke out in 2003, her mother sent her to the countryside as a 1-year-old to protect her. Now, she didn't want to wallow in anxiety and depression, and she wanted to protect something.
The Chinese student population in Singapore is not very large. After entering the group, Wen Tan Yi looked at the group members and found that there were no other Wuhan people besides himself, which meant the donor team could not meet the needs of the local hospital in Wuhan. She added "looks like a person in charge" to Huang's wechat.
"My father has just donated something, and the parents of my classmates are doctors in Wuhan. So I would like to make some suggestions. First of all, it's not very recommended to donate money. They don't need money, they need things that money can't buy, " she told Huang, the N95 mask was the most wanted item for front line doctors, followed by hydrogen peroxide. Soon, Wen Tan was also invited by Huang Lei Ke planning small group.
Three people never crossed paths before. If it wasn't for the new crown disease, Huang should be preparing for his chosen political science major by previewing the prince, the wealth of nations and the end of history and the last man. Liu Yan ru will accompany grandparents to watch TV, chat. Because studying abroad, she has not returned to accompany them for four years. And Wen tan-yi, no accident, then, or as before, star-chasing, make friends, "nest in their own circle whisper. ".
But the outbreak changed everything.

❷

Ignorance and fearlessness

For several days, Huang has been using the screen for nearly 10 hours, with the longest day being 12 hours. January 26, more than 8:00 a.m. , because of the lack of sleep for several days, Wen Tan Yi did not stay up, prone to sleep on the dormitory table. When I woke up an hour later, there were more than 600 unread messages on Wechat from the Fund Raising Coordination Group and three large groups of fund raisers. At home in Xiamen, Liu Yanru has been processing messages in bed nonstop since she opened her eyes and grabbed her mobile phone at 7 am. Her parents were almost angry when they told her to have breakfast.

Since the New Year's Eve decision to raise money for the hospital, this has become the norm for the three of them.
Donations are moving too fast. When he decided to raise money, Huang was aiming for just $4,000, just enough to buy a box of N95 masks like those at the grocery store downstairs. He knew nothing about material standards and the like, and his only judgement was: "eight dollars a piece, quite expensive, must be up to standard. "
The fund-raising focus first on Singapore students who have dealt with them in the past. Huang has been involved in the preparation of two Singapore Spring Festival gala and in an NGO called "Emergence Chung Fund" , which incubates student groups. So he started with students who had worked on both projects.
Less than 9 pm on New Year's Eve, Huang Leike posted a Qr Code on the wechat group of Singaporean students, announcing the formation of a "Wuhan Donation Group of Singaporean Wuhan Students" for fund-raising. "We have found a mask shop, a box 500,4,000 RMB, I hope everyone together to donate! If there is no supply, just donate! " The number of people scanning into the crowd.
A succession of crises soon emerged. First, the suppliers of face masks that have just passed wechat verification are out of stock. Huang Lei Ke felt the pressure for the first time. "When you started the group, you told people you had a source to buy masks, but now they're out of stock. " After that, he consulted with other organizers in the Coordination Group about whether to donate money directly, as agreed, if the source was not found.
"supplies are actually more useful than money, " demurred one member of the Coordination Group.
"I think the supplies will not only be unlucky, they will be Information asymmetry, " objected another member.
"supplies can not be bought. " Huang Leike was a little depressed.
Wen Tan Yi just into the group, see these three on the discussion of supplies, put with a front-line doctor wechat communication screenshot into the Coordination Group: supplies are the most scarce and most urgent.
"But the question is what Wuhan needs, not what we can offer. " After several rounds of communication, we finally reached an agreement on how to donate: supplies, masks, goggles and gloves.
At that time, there were less than 10 people in the "fund-raising and Donation Coordination Center" for the planning and conducting of the party. There were only four or five people who really focused on talking about doing something. Huang Leike took the news of "Hubei Urgent Request for help" published by "Hubei Voice" as a reference for the function and protection standard of materials.
Source of goods, we can only separate to think of ways: Huang Lei Ke through friends and relatives looking for mask manufacturers, the rest of the people separately to the major e-commerce platform search. There are three screening conditions: meet the Protection Standards; Spring Festival Shipment; can be transported to Wuhan and surrounding areas through the Shunfeng Green Channel. The supply of face masks that meet this condition is very limited. Even if satisfied, the qualification of the supplier and the quality of the mask can not be guaranteed. "This is the mask that sends a line after all, the standard wants very high ability. " Liu Yan ru first time feels" despairing" .
Huang Lei Ke told the truth in large groups. A group of friends proposed to buy from overseas, but Huang rejected it: "The Spring Festival Customs holiday, plus mail and customs clearance time. " Some insisted that we should try to find masks. Huang Lei Ke reminds: "all materials are needed, not only the mask is badly needed. " Is a few rounds of discussion, we decided to "main attack" supplies of relatively adequate goggles and gloves.
Wen Tan remembers that night, everyone separately inquired about 80 shops. Some stores "Lion's Share" , but some stores heard that is donated to Wuhan Materials, the initiative to reduce prices. In the end, a few people sifted through more than 200 stores to find fewer than 10 sources.
Voices of doubt have been heard sporadically from unknown donors. How do we prove the source? How do I know you're who you say you are? How does the money flow?
"We have nothing. If you don't believe us, then don't. I can't prove it to you. You can wait and see for a while until we complete the first purchase, and if you still have questions, you can consider withdrawing from the group."Huang Leike chose the simplest way to respond.
That night, everyone worked until 2:30 in the morning. Huang Lei Ke remembers that he put a paragraph of edited good goggles to ask to send 30 times on jd.com, do not have inn reply. January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, 7:00 am, there is a reply available. He paid $5,500 for all 200 pairs to Wuhan Union Hospital -- Foshan -- and then sent screenshots of the order to fund raisers, with budgets ranging from $15,000 to $20,000.
At about the same time, the first fundraising group was full, and more people asked to join the group. They soon formed a second group. At 10:20 am, the team puts the code into the collection box and announces the start of the collection. Money poured in, and Liu's phone started vibrating, with amounts ranging from 100 yuan to 2,000 yuan, the most common being between 200 yuan and 500 yuan, with messages such as "refueling in Wuhan. ".
In order to lock the source of supply, Huang Lei Ke has long authorized Liu Yan ru to place orders at any time. So, at 10:57 a.m. , Liu placed a second order for 39.9 yuan worth of medical gloves, in accordance with the requirements of circular No. 4"Unified Deployment" issued by the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Prevention and control headquarters on donation methods, to the Red Cross in Wuhan. At 12:04, the third order, 250 pairs of goggles at 26 yuan each, was sent to Wuhan Tongji Hospital. At 12:09, the fourth order, the same goggles, was sent to the Wuhan Union Hospital. 12:24, fifth pen, sent to the First People's Hospital of Xiaogan city. 13:58, the sixth pen, sent to Yichang First People's hospital. 14:07, the seventh, to the First People's Hospital in Xiantao. 15:04, the eighth pen, sent to the First Hospital of Wuhan.

The first round of fundraising and material purchases took less than seven hours from the official launch to the announcement. At 16:30, the first batch of material purchase, account liquidation is over, Huang Lei Ke announced the details in the donation crowd: a total of 15,000 pairs of gloves, 1,450 goggles. The balance was $3,410.31, which several organizers raised to $5,100 out of their own pockets. They're going to donate all the money to the charity of Wuhan.
Underwrite the first order of time, Huang Lei Ke thought of this money "may not come back. ". But he soon realized that raising money wasn't that hard. At the end of the first round, they received 53,000 yuan, far more than expected.
What's really hard is finding a source that meets the standards for protection. First-line doctors sometimes demand more than the official standard. In theory, with the same level of protection, first-line doctors prefer to use N95 over KN95. Liu finds many "pits" that need to be carefully circumvented. For example, care needs to be taken to verify whether the object carries a breathing valve, which can not be used by first-line medical personnel. Some retailers may recommend 3m masks for 9501 and 9502, but they are mainly anti-smog. Goggles to choose anti-fog, this will not affect the clinical operation of medical staff.

In overcoming the "despair" of the process, Liu Yanru has been able to recite a variety of material standards. At any moment during an interview, she would recite a long list of numbers. "9132,1860,4565,1621AF, really, these days it's more fun to see than anything else, it's like hitting the Jackpot, " she wrote on her friends' network.
Raffles Junior College Graduate Liu Yanru
Harder still is deciding who to give the supplies to. Wen Tan Yi docking hospital, each hospital told her: "We are too short. ". In addition to the first to consider the concord, Tongji, the People's hospital three, she can only consider directly to the hospital. The acquaintance society comes into play. An international student from Yichang reached out to a Yichang hospital, and Yichang was considered. Wun tan-yi's mother is a Xiaogan who has direct access to a hospital in Xiaogan, so it can be added to the list. Others say they can not be admitted because the hospital is short of supplies, so hospitals can be contacted immediately.
In short, there is not much time to think about analysis, can only rely on a limited acquaintance recommendation, comprehensive consideration of logistics, geographical balance, with intuition to make a quick decision.

The parents of a middle school classmate were doctors at two hospitals in concord and Tongji. After the donation was sent out, the classmate's father went to the class wechat group to thank her. That long Wechat, he said a lot of "thank you. ". Wen cried when she saw it. "Our little effort is not worth the gratitude of the doctors on the front line. I can't imagine how hard the medical staff is working now. They shouldn't have to endure this. "

"9132,1860,4565,1621AF, really, these days it's more fun to see than anything else, it's like hitting the Jackpot, " she wrote on her friends' network.

Raffles Junior College Graduate Liu Yanru

Harder still is deciding who to give the supplies to. Wen Tan Yi docking hospital, each hospital told her: "We are too short. ". In addition to the first to consider the concord, Tongji, the People's hospital three, she can only consider directly to the hospital. The acquaintance society comes into play. An international student from Yichang reached out to a Yichang hospital, and Yichang was considered. Wun tan-yi's mother is a Xiaogan who has direct access to a hospital in Xiaogan, so it can be added to the list. Others say they can not be admitted because the hospital is short of supplies, so hospitals can be contacted immediately.

In short, there is not much time to think about analysis, can only rely on a limited acquaintance recommendation, comprehensive consideration of logistics, geographical balance, with intuition to make a quick decision.

The parents of a middle school classmate were doctors at two hospitals in concord and Tongji. After the donation was sent out, the classmate's father went to the class wechat group to thank her. That long Wechat, he said a lot of "thank you. ". Wen cried when she saw it. "Our little effort is not worth the gratitude of the doctors on the front line. I can't imagine how hard the medical staff is working now. They shouldn't have to endure this. "

###

❸

The mysterious Mr. Wang

#

The second round of fundraising begins on the third night of the Lunar New Year. The team set a fundraising goal of 50,000. Those who can start have already donated one round. Huang's expectations for the second round are very low. "Maybe only twenty thousand will be raised. "

Still in dire need of supplies, they decided to hold on to as many as they could to fund the hospital -- a "mysterious Mr. Wang. ".

No one knows who Mr. Wang is or how he got into the group. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Mr. Wang added Huang Leike's Wechat, and asked him to bank account number and account name.
Huang Lei Ke feels strange: Weixin transfers me not to be good?
Wechat doesn't work, Mr. Wang said.
Huang Lei Ke said, why, how much do you want to donate?
Mr. Wang said 100,000.
Huang Lei Ke hurriedly rejects, "startled. "
And Mr. Wang said, thirty thousand. Huang Lei Ke still didn't dare to take it. In the end, he took 10 grand.
Mr. Wang doesn't ask for anything, he just wants to donate money. The second round of fund-raising exceeded expectations, they and Mr. Wang reached a tacit understanding, no more money, the material links and hospital address sent to him directly, let him order, is a personal donation.
In hindsight, the team found that Mr. Wang alone had purchased nearly $100,000 worth of goggles, the largest amount, $55,000, and sent 1,000 goggles to the Wuhan Union Hospital, the rest went to the community health service centers in Xiaogan, Xiantao and Wuhan.
Just as a virus needs a super-spreader to spread, they are raising money for "super-contributors" such as Mr Wang. With the exception of the second order, they sent everything directly to the hospital, and the fastest one, from purchase to receipt, took only four days.
On February 1, after public opinion focused on the Red Cross, Huang Lei Ke couldn't help but post a receipt for supplies issued by the Wuhan Union Hospital. "As a provincial Red Cross Society, it is not as efficient as our group of high school and college students, " he wrote in the group
"I'm the one who wants to do something. I won't feel comfortable until I see the people who really need it get the supplies. " In an interview, Mr. Wang explained why he chose the high school students. He himself was a Chinese student in Singapore.
Not Without incident. January 26, fund-raising two groups of a group of friends told Wen Yaoyi, a person claiming to be organizers add people privately, send Qr Code fund-raising. Wungo immediately apologized to the group. After consultation, the Planning Group decided to make public the names, schools and contact details of all the organizers, and to clarify them in a unified group. In order to strengthen the management, in the large group, each organizer has added the "administrator" label before the remarks.
"Open and transparent can solve the problem and answer the question, " Wen tan-yi later concluded.
Wen Yaoyi, 18, a freshman at Raffles Junior College, is from Wuhan.
Donations from Singaporean students are not huge. At the end of January, more influential North American students "million masks" , "Wuhan refueling" projects have been exposed materials substandard.
"I think it's just a farce. Maybe some of them really want to do something for the motherland, but more of them seem to do it for publicity and publicity. The weirdest thing is, every time you retweet it, you donate an extra mask. It's so urgent, everyone's rushing to get masks to the epidemic area, and they still have time to wait around for them to be forwarded? Masks do not meet the standards of things even more speechless, labor and waste of money. It would be easy to criticize them if we didn't do it ourselves. But now, I don't think it's that hard to find a manufacturer that meets the standard. I don't understand how they can do such a good thing,"Huang said.

❹

Real World Enlightenment

January 23, learned that Wuhan's most "cattle" of the three hospitals actually began to social fund-raising, Wen Tan Yi has concluded: rumors, false.

But later, when her father, who often travels to Xinjiang on business, has even started to look for a mask supplier in Xinjiang to support frontline doctors, Wen finally believes that it is true. "I knew something was wrong. My whole heart was bleeding, angry, helpless and anxious to do something. "
Winsome has cried many times. She cries when she receives letters of thanks from her classmates'doctor parents, when she sees the empty city video posted by Vlogger in Wuhan, and when she sees the community in Wuhan collectively singing the national anthem. There is no other way, the simplest way is to "get busy, do something for Wuhan. ".
In the interview, Chai Jing, a former journalist for news investigation, recalled an experience during SARS when a female doctor was dazed by the severity of the outbreak and muttered, "my child is only 3 years old. ". But in an isolated dormitory, she went to comfort the panicked female students. When she got out of the House, she told Chai Jing, "I am a mother, too, " and Chai Jing wrote, "it is only when one cares about others that one forgets himself.
"I know that book! " Wen tan-yi said. "I must make it big, " she said, "No matter what people around me say, I must receive the money and make sure it gets to hospitals in Wuhan and surrounding cities. ".
In her first year of junior high school in Singapore, she took a general education class on social stratification, where the teacher led discussions about social class and mobility. After the outbreak, looking at the plight of different people, she recalled the class discussion, "some groups do not get masks, which is related to social stratification. "
Wen tan-yi is still in suspense. Because there's a lot of supplies that aren't getting to the hospital. She was worried that something would happen, and she kept tracking the logistics.
Previously, Huang Leike thought that reading at home was the most important thing. But now, he would use "read a few books" to describe that kind of closed-door reading state. "In another 10 or 20 years, when I think back to the epidemic, when everyone else was hiding at home brushing their mobile phones, I can say with a clear conscience that I'm not counting the grains of rice in my house, how many hairs my cat has, I'm with some friends and I'm doing something for the doctor ahead, " Huang said.
On January 30, the team announced the end of operation protector fundraising under the name of "Emergence Chung Fund" . The organizers have expanded from a few to 14. The group raised 130,000 yuan for charity and purchased 24 batches of supplies. They have published receipts and Payments Accounts, orders, hospital receipts and logistics records through graphite documents and wechat public accounts. The balance of 3,400 yuan, they donated to the Alumni Association of Wuhan University, Please take their place.
"How can it be? Amazing. " Liu's mother, Chen Jing (not her real name) , marveled at the success of the first round of donations. "That's a matter for the central government, " Chen Jing said at first, without retorting. When it was done, Chen Jing felt her daughter was "connected" to a real world of problems and risks.
Ms. Liu had previously been averse to social expansion, but in hindsight, she was amazed at the energy that comes from bonding with strangers. All along, because of peer pressure, Liu Yanru likes to use "slag" to describe himself. She repeatedly stressed her "ordinary" . But in the process of organizing her donations, she found a sense of worth.
Wen tan-yi said, "I was in a competition once where I had to introduce myself, and I didn't know what to say, so I scraped together the number of words and said my dream was to change the world. I'm an extrovert, but I never make a move. Until this thing, now, I know I can make a difference."
